article.title: Casino Resorts in Indiana

metatags.og:description: In Indiana, all casinos must be located on riverboats docked along a waterway. While many people are working to close the casinos, the subject is a touchy one as the gaming industry is the fifth largest in the state. Because the casinos themselves are built on water, the associated hotels and restaurants are built along the docks, in close proximity to the casino they serve.
